{"word":"θεόθεν","slug":"θεόθεν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θεόθεν</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <a href='S:-θεν'><el>-θεν</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>old <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> of <el>θεός</el>, used as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>from the gods, at the hands of the gods</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>divinitus</el>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>by the help</i> or <i>favour of the gods</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <i>by the gods</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}